gobblin.compaction.verify

Class DataCompletenessVerifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • gobblin.compaction.verify.DataCompletenessVerifier
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable

    public class DataCompletenessVerifier
extends Object
implements Closeable
    A class for verifying data completeness of a Dataset. To verify data completeness, one should extend DataCompletenessVerifier.AbstractRunner and implement Callable.call() which returns a DataCompletenessVerifier.Results object. The (fully qualified) name of the class that extends DataCompletenessVerifier.AbstractRunner should be associated with property ConfigurationKeys#COMPACTION_DATA_COMPLETENESS_VERIFICATION_CLASS.
